                <p>The benefit is calculated based on your insured salary and is normally paid in the form of <strong>daily compensation</strong>. As an order of magnitude, we usually speak of a rate of <strong>70%</strong> of the insured salary, or <strong>80%</strong> in certain cases (for example, with dependent children). There are maximum limits and specific rules on bonuses, extra pay, part-time work, etc.</p>
